split_lines = []
for line in lines:
    split_line = line.split(',')
    split_lines.append(split_line)
    #print(split_line)

#Split out the elements in the line for cleanup
full_printout = ''
for line in split_lines[0:15]:
    i = 1
    printout = ''
    print('\n\n')
    for item in line:
        #Rnk
        if i == 1:
            new_item = '(' + item + ','
            print(new_item)
            printout += new_item
        #Player
        if i == 2:
            new_item = '\'' + item.replace('\'', '\'\'') + '\','
            print(new_item)
            printout += new_item
        i+= 1
    full_printout += '\n' + printout
full_printout
